Traffic and law enforcement services have been deployed to Khayelitsha, on the Cape Flats, where sporadic protests have broken out. It is unclear what the protests are about at this stage. Cape Town Traffic Services spokesperson Kevin Jacobs says several roads have been closed. Jacobs says, “Cape Town Traffic Officers are attending to incidents protest action in the Khayelitsha area this morning. The following roads are closed in Khayelitsha; Baden Powell drive is closed at Swartklip road. Baden Powell Drive is closed at Mew Way. Motorists are advised to use alternative routes.”